You could implement a `size` method using recursion.
If `root` is `null` (stack is empty) return `0`.

Else call recursive `private` `size` method. If your current `Node` has next `Node` call `size` method on next `Node` and increment `size` variable by one. If there is no next `Node` just return the counted `size`. 
```java
    public int size() {
        return root != null
                ? size(root, 1)
                : 0;
    }

    private int size(Node node, int size) {
        Node next = node.getNext();
        return next != null
                ? size(next, size + 1)
                : size;
    }
```

